The paper discusses the creation of a dataset for scientific entity extraction, classification, and resolution in a multidisciplinary context, with a focus on STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering, and Medicine) disciplines. The paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, such as BERT-based neural models, and encyclopedic entity linking and lexicographic word sense disambiguation. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DL (Machine Learning).
